rking on other graphical games.  Also, radar does not read from your ram.  It parses the inbound socket stream.  DAoC changes the encryption, not the placement.  DAoC has also put in things to counter the cheating (DLL footprint detection etc).  What truly needs to be done is very simple but DAoC would never do it.  Random screen shots taken by the client during play when the DAoC window is in the foreground.  Many gaming companies have done this.  IE: PunkBuster and Counterstrike.  DAoC for fear of invading a customer's privacy would never step to this level, however.  I firmly believe this should be implemented though. <br> <p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr align="right" valign="bottom"><td colspan=2 class="BoardRowB"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/post.asp?brd=5176&topic=85711421">Post Reply</a> | <a href="/active_topic_notify.asp?mes=86338065" class="BoardRowBLink">Active Topic Notification</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/pm_send.asp?usr=1041180">Private Message</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/user_posts.asp?usr=1041180">Post History</a></td></tr><tr align="left" valign="top" class="BoardRowA"><td class="BoardRowA" rowspan=3 width="17%"><a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/Babaloooo?boards=vn " class="AuthorLink">Babaloooo</a>&nbsp;<a href="/Help/Faqs.aspx#stars"><img align=absmiddle src=/images/star4.gif border=0 hspace=0 vspace=0 alt="4,170 posts"></a><br><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><!-- WISH & COLL STUFF --><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr class="BoardRowA"><td nowrap="false" class="BoardRowA"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/collection/Babaloooo"><font size="1">collection (0)</font></a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/wishlist/Babaloooo"><font size="1">wishlist (0)</font></a></td></tr></table><!-- /WISH & COLL STUFF	--><span style="font-weight: bold;">Posts:</span> 4,170<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Registered:</span> Aug 02<br></span><br></td><td class="BoardRowA" colspan=2 width=